A_405 - Sometimes it may happen that someone in our vicinity does not want us to do something (e.g. drink a coffee at home). What happens is that what doesn't seem like a problem to us is actually a problem for those close to us because due to a series of circumstances that are difficult to calculate, their perception of that gesture (but above all of the effects it causes in their own life) is different from what we think and which we are unlikely to be aware of. Sometimes, however, when a choice is strongly discouraged, the truth is that there are a range of many other possible choices that we can make, without necessarily being stubborn in wanting to do exactly that. It is not difficult to understand that when another person gets angry about our possible direction it is because that person feels bad or uncomfortable because has already experienced it in the past and it was not pleasant...